    "created_at": "2015-06-29T17:03:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-29T17:03:32Z",
    "body": "It looks like currently pepper API support is specifically implemented for Flash via the `--ppapi-flash-path` and `--ppapi-flash-version` command line switch. I haven't been able to find support for the generic `--register-pepper-plugins` chromium command line switch. Does this exist and I am just missing it? It looks like the underlying pepper api support is in the codebase, just not the handling of the command line switch. Any additional information would be great!\n"
  },
